uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.session.twofactor

Class TwoFactorHandler<A extends AppUser>

  • java.lang.Object
    • uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.session.twofactor.TwoFactorHandler<A>

  • public class TwoFactorHandler<A extends AppUser>
extends java.lang.Object
    Handle two-factor authorisation plugins. This is only appropriate for explicit login control-flows. It is inserted at the point where the person would be set in the session. If two factor is enabled the person is remembered and the two-factor verification flow invoked instead. If we use external-auth enabled on any location we need to invoke via a required-page instead
